Terrorismo

Bajo el tituar El terrorismo que el mundo hered del 11 de septiembre de El Colombiano del da domingo 11 de septiembre de 2016 en las pginas 4 y 5 aparce la siguiente grfica:

Exploracin y descripcin

terr <- read.csv2("terrorismo.csv")
barplot(t(as.matrix(terr[,c(4,5)])), beside = TRUE)

barplot(t(as.matrix(terr[,c(2,3)])), beside = TRUE)

barplot(t(as.matrix(terr[,2:4])), beside = TRUE)

require(ggplot2)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
g1 <- ggplot(terr, aes(Ao, vict_atent))
g1 + geom_bar(stat = "identity")

require(ggplot2)
g1 <- ggplot(terr, aes(Ao, vict_suicid))
g1 + geom_bar(stat = "identity")

require(ggplot2)
g1 <- ggplot(terr, aes(Ao, num_atent))
g1 + geom_bar(stat = "identity")

require(ggplot2)
g1 <- ggplot(terr, aes(Ao, num_suicid))
g1 + geom_bar(stat = "identity")

terr$vict_x_atent <- with(terr, vict_atent/num_atent * 100)
terr$vict_x_suicid <- with(terr, vict_suicid/num_suicid * 100)

require(tidyr)
## Loading required package: tidyr
require(dplyr)
## Loading required package: dplyr
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
terr2 <- terr %>% 
         select(Ao, vict_x_atent, vict_x_suicid) %>% 
         gather(tipo, indice, c(vict_x_atent, vict_x_suicid))
require(ggplot2)
g1 <- ggplot(terr2, aes(Ao, indice, col = tipo))
g1 + geom_line()

g1 <- ggplot(terr2, aes(Ao, indice, col = tipo))
g1 + geom_line(size = 1.5) +
     ggtitle("Porcentaje de vctimas por tipo de atentado") +
     scale_x_continuous(breaks = unique(terr2$Ao)) +
     scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,26,2)) +
     ylab("Porcentaje (%)") +
     theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
